      "content": {
        "title": "Advanced Musculoskeletal Imaging — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Cross-sectional and functional imaging modalities including CT, MRI, bone scan, and PET applied to musculoskeletal disorders.",
        "summary": "MRI excels for soft tissue and marrow edema. CT provides fracture detail and arthroplasty planning. Bone scan detects occult stress injury and metastases."
      },
